Let R be Equivalence relation on a set X. Then we define the Quotient set
X/R := \{[a]\mid  a\in  X\}
is the set of equivalence classes. We have a natural surjective map X\to  X/R sending a\mapsto [a].

Let b_{1},b_{2}\in  A be inverses for a. Then
\begin {align} b_{1}&=\mu (b_{1},e)\\ &=\mu (b_{1},\mu (a,b_{2}))\\ &=\mu (\mu (b_{1},a),b_{2})\hbox { by associativity}\\ &=\mu (e,b_{2})\\ &=b_{2}.\end {align}
Hence the result.

